In this article, NSC spokesperson Caitlin Hayden discusses a meeting between Deputy National Security Advisor Tony Blinken and Bahraini Crown Prince and First Deputy Prime Minister Prince Salman bin Hamad Al-Khalifa. President Obama joined the meeting and reaffirmed the importance of the partnership between the United States and Bahrain. The President congratulated the Crown Prince on his appointment and emphasized U.S. support for Bahrain's stability and security. The President also stressed the need for meaningful reform, dialogue, and respect for human rights as the best path to achieving peace and security in Bahrain. The President expressed support for Bahrain's National Dialogue and encouraged all sides to engage constructively. The President commended the Crown Prince's commitment to advancing reform and assured continued support from the United States. A photo of the meeting is provided in the article.